 ACT
125
Unworthiness to inherit
He is unworthy to inherit, both by law and by will, as well as to receive anything by will:
1. the one who intentionally killed the testator, or attempted to do so;
2. the one who forced the testator to make or revoke a will or a testamentary provision by force or threat, or prevented him from doing so;
3. the one who destroyed or hid the testator's will with the intention of preventing the execution of the testator's last will, as well as the one who falsified the testator's will;
4. the one who made a serious mistake about the maintenance obligation towards the testator towards whom he had a legal obligation to maintain, the one who did not want to provide the testator with the necessary help, which he could have provided without endangering his own life, or left him without help in circumstances that dangerous to life or health.
